All narrowPeak files in narrowPeak directory processed by run_homer_on_dir.sh > results directory (copied and renamed from HALPER pipeline output, species specific coordinates)

    Output organized as follows:

    Results/
        Folder for specific sample/
            peaks_homer.bed
            annotated_peaks.txt
            annotatePeaks.log
            findMotifs.log
            motifs/
                several files from findPeaksGenome.pl

    Relevant outputs included:

        peaks_homer.bed: convered narrowPeak files to BED files that homer can use

        annotated_peaks.txt: tab-delimited file of peak annotations including id, coordinates, genomic feature (promoter, intronic, etc.), distance from nearest TSS, nearest gene IDs

        knownMotifs.txt and .html: known motif enrichment table

    AI DISCLAIMER: the script used to generate these outputs (run_homer_on_dir.sh) was modified from that generated by Claude.ai

All annotated_peaks.txt files in results/subdir processed by extract_promoters_enhancers.sh > peak_types

    Output: a text files with the peak id and promoter/enhancer label as determined by the HOMER annotation combined with the distance from TSS (>= 2000 bp for introns/intergenic annotation --> enhancer)

    Text files in peak_types visualized by plot_promoters_enhancers.R and put in same folder as .png
